As of milestone M1 of ADR-032 ("Embed solid-pod-rs as Rust library"),
the webxr workspace consumes the following AGPL-3.0-only Rust crates
from the solid-pod-rs workspace (co-maintained with the upstream
JavaScriptSolidServer project by DreamLab-AI):

  * solid-pod-rs        — LDP resources, WAC, NIP-98, fs-backend,
                          Solid Notifications 0.2
  * solid-pod-rs-nostr  — did:nostr resolver, NIP-05 endpoint,
                          Schnorr verifier
  * solid-pod-rs-idp    — Pod and key provisioning

Linking these crates makes the combined webxr binary AGPL-3.0-only.
The webxr workspace itself is therefore AGPL-3.0-only as of M1.

Pre-M1 history was distributed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0
(retained at LICENSE.MPL for reference). The relicense is recorded
in docs/adr/ADR-032-embed-solid-pod-rs-library.md.

Network-corresponding-source obligation under AGPL §13 is satisfied
by the public source repository URL exposed via the server-info HTTP
header `X-Source-URL` and the `/.well-known/solid` document
(wired in M2-M5).

